00:02:41.500 --> 00:02:43.380
to be quite severe.

00:02:43.380 --> 00:02:45.913
And when we talk about internal states,

00:02:46.840 --> 00:02:49.580
we use that term to
distinguish from externalizing

00:02:49.580 --> 00:02:52.230
behaviors, so things that
we typically think about

00:02:52.230 --> 00:02:56.660
when we are thinking about
outbursts or tantrums

00:02:56.660 --> 00:02:58.930
or dysregulated behavior.

00:02:58.930 --> 00:03:03.930
And so the issues are
complicated in that again

00:03:05.080 --> 00:03:07.340
these symptoms are internal.

00:03:07.340 --> 00:03:11.700
And so clinicians tend to be unaccustomed

00:03:11.700 --> 00:03:16.620
to even considering these
symptoms in the setting

00:03:16.620 --> 00:03:18.680
of neurodevelopmental disorders.

00:03:18.680 --> 00:03:23.160
Again they're not obvious and so they tend

00:03:23.160 --> 00:03:25.190
to go unrecognized.

00:03:25.190 --> 00:03:28.500
And then when and if they are recognized,

00:03:28.500 --> 00:03:30.750
then we are also facing this issue

00:03:30.750 --> 00:03:35.300
of diagnostic overshadowing
which means these symptoms

00:03:35.300 --> 00:03:38.260
basically get attributed to the
neurodevelopmental disorder.

00:03:38.260 --> 00:03:41.810
They're not seen as something
different or separate

00:03:41.810 --> 00:03:43.673
from the neurodevelopmental disorder.

00:03:44.860 --> 00:03:49.860
And then even more important I
think than this clarification

00:03:50.920 --> 00:03:54.730
of the symptoms is the idea
that when these symptoms

00:03:54.730 --> 00:03:59.730
go unrecognized, they cause
a great deal of suffering.

00:03:59.900 --> 00:04:04.900
And related to that suffering is morbidity

00:04:06.240 --> 00:04:10.310
that is unnecessary because
these symptoms can be treated

00:04:10.310 --> 00:04:12.750
and hence the third point.

00:04:12.750 --> 00:04:15.060
Effective treatment does exist.

00:04:15.060 --> 00:04:18.993
And so that will be the focus
of my presentation today.

